## Preface

“Once upon a time, I, Zhuangzi, was unconscious of my individuality as a man. Suddenly, I awoke, and there I lay, myself again. Now I do not know whether I was then a man dreaming I was a butterfly, or whether I am now a butterfly, dreaming I am a man. Between a man and a butterfly, there is a barrier. The transition is called Metempsychosis, or the transmigration of the soul.” – Zhuangzi

![][image2]

### **A Vivid Dream and a New Understanding**

I awoke suddenly, heart pounding, from a dream so vivid it felt more real than reality. It’s 3:30 in the morning, and I find myself lying in our tent next to my nine-year-old son, who is deeply asleep, nestled in his blankets. We’re camping at the edge of the woods behind our home on the first full day of spring, under a moonless sky. I am waking from a twilight dream with a realization that fills me with wonder. In the dream, I am the elements—alive, aware, and weaving through this moment.

I am flame and ember, illuminating the dark. I am rain and dew, nurturing the blossoms. I am soil and trees, rooted, branching, and taking form. I am wind and breath, singing new life. It was like experiencing firsthand one of those science documentaries revealing the secret life of the world around us—except I was all of it. What a rush\! The world is alive, and I am a living part of it, woven into its flow with my own. All is one.

This dream reminds me that the natural world is the foundation of all human consciousness, not just something onto which we project our thoughts, feelings, and intentions. In this moment, everything that separated me from the natural world has dissipated into a dynamic field of being, completely integrated into it, an at-oneness. For the first time in my life, I feel truly a part of it all. No longer am I certain if I am dreaming of the elements or if I am the elements dreaming me. How had I missed this knowing?

***"**If your heart is truly open, then all of nature, life, and experience is the mystery of interconnection and opportunity for communion." \- Michael A. Singer*

My being, my heart, and my aspirations all arise from a field of presence, which feels both vast and intimate, infinite and finite. Whatever felt foreign, alien, or disconnected in me before has now resolved into an expansive state of peace, harmony, and love.

Reflecting on my dream, I am enchanted by this direct experience of the elements and how they give rise to the most basic aspects of my human awareness. My intuition, like fire, enlightens my being. My emotions, like water, flow deeply. My senses, like the earth, are rooted and embodied. My mind, like air, permeates everything, with thoughts swirling around me.

At the heart of everything is my soul’s constant presence, ephemeral like aether, still, formless, and abiding, brought to life by the divine orchestration of the other elements dancing around and through me.

Being enveloped in the elements of nature is a magical experience. The elements aren’t discrete things but commingling aspects of a dynamic, intelligent world at play. This means that when I’m exploring this world, I too am at play. The life force within me is the same life force animating all of existence, and it is exhilarating.

Standing in the grasses outside the tent, I realized I embody the living elements and that everything is interconnected. This moment of heightened awareness showed me the layers of experience woven together. For me, the layers were woven into a single, phenomenal, elemental few moments of heightened awareness.

The feeling of stepping barefoot on the dew that has settled in the grass is exhilarating. I raise my arms overhead and stretch, breathing cool air deeply into my lungs. A feeling of deep calm has come over me. This is home, the state of being I’ve been seeking for a lifetime. My emotions are high. My senses are reeling. And my mind gives way to this moment. One with it all.

The sound of the chimes outside the tent, announcing the mercurial nature of the wind, reflecting the nature of my mind in its constant state of flux. The crickets sang a chorus of ancient “hymns,” soothing my soul and transforming my perception of the world from harshness into splendor. The cool air on my face and hands hinted at a change in season from winter to spring. The sight of my young son lying peacefully asleep in the early dawn filled me with love. It was a peak moment, the stuff of which dreams and memories are made.

How wonderful it is to experience the dynamism of life as a never-ending dance of creative expression in which spirit, emotions, body, and mind actively participate as complementary, intertwined forces. When I have peak moments, as I do periodically, I feel myself both drawn in and projected out onto a presence profoundly animated and alive. And I imagine that this enigmatic presence, life force, or dynamic is the expression of the living God all seekers are seeking.

If there is a source of all wisdom and all creativity, I believe it would be infused with a lively natural intelligence that constantly informs all of these layers of our consciousness.

My heightened state of being after dreaming of the elements reminded me of what my life was like when I was my son’s age, a time when I felt deeply in love with, fascinated by, and connected to nature. I lived it, breathed it, and dreamed about it. The world back then was an enchanted adventure inviting me to be fully present within it. Life was beautiful, magical, and mysterious. This must be how my son feels when he’s trying to coax me away from my work to play with insects and trees and splash about in the streams.

***“**May what I do flow from me like a river, no forcing and no holding back, the way it is with children.” — Rainer Maria Rilke*

I remember as a young boy returning home after a full day immersed in the enchanted woods, only to be struck by the sudden sense of melancholy that pervaded the dining room as my parents grappled with the weight of a heavy situation. Witnessing their distress was shocking and upsetting. Although I never did learn what the problem was, I registered how they appeared in that moment and reflected deeply upon it. They felt different from me. They weren’t enchanted by the forests like I was. They were suffering something I didn’t understand.

There was a stark contrast between their experience and mine. We were in different worlds although sharing the same physical space. I was high on life and feeling the enchantment of nature. They were weighed down by a catastrophe to which only adults were privy. Adulthood seemed like a hellish state to be in. I knew I wanted to avoid the same fate if possible. I wanted to be able to choose to be in a more enchanted and peaceful world.

*"It may be that when we no longer know what to do we have come to our real work, and that when we no longer know which way to go, we have begun our real journey. The mind that is not baffled is not employed. The impeded stream is the one that sings." – Wendell Berry*

Like my own children, I was conscious enough to ask critical questions in my youth about my parents’ unhappiness, like What’s wrong here? How did they become like this? Will this also be my fate when I am an adult? Is this what my children will one day see in me? If so, can I change it?

Now I can see that, as hard as my life has been at times, everything that has occurred over the years has made me a better person. As much as I’d like to go back and take away my younger self’s suffering in certain challenging circumstances, if I did, I’d be denying myself the opportunity to become the more soulful, fully human person I am today. How I’ve worked with the challenges of earthly living, rather than wishing them away, is a blessing. I’ve learned that it isn’t about avoiding life’s challenges and its twists and turns, but about the quality of our presence, the way we show up for these experiences, and how we manage them that matters most.

*“Life is a game of just five ingredients. Even a pizza requires more ingredients\! But in yoga both the human body and the cosmos are based on the magic of only five elements- earth, water, fire, and ether. Such a staggeringly complex phenomenon and just five variables\! Not surprisingly, those who attained self-realization have often termed life a cosmic joke. . . Every spiritual practice in the world is related in some way with organizing these five elements.” \- Sadhguru*

### Reflection and Interaction

* Reflect on a recent experience where you felt a profound connection to nature. Consider how each aspect of conscious awareness—intuition, emotions, senses, thoughts, and Spirit—manifested during that moment, shaping your perception and the experience itself.  
* Spend time in nature, intentionally engaging with each element of conscious awareness. Observe how they influence your thoughts, emotions, and physical sensations. Journal your experiences and any insights you gain from this mindful interaction.

### Call to Adventure

*“As you start to walk on the way, the way appears.” \- Rumi*

This book is a collection of interconnected insights, conversations, and experiences I wish had been shared with me when I started my journey of awakening. It honors the power of direct experience and directed, developed attention. The advice, strategies, and ways of interpreting reality are offered as insights from my experience. They may not fit your own reality tunnel. As the Buddha advises in the Kalama Sutta:

*"Do not believe in anything simply because you have heard it. Do not believe in traditions because they have been handed down for many generations. Do not believe anything because it is spoken and rumored by many. Do not believe in anything simply because it is found written in your religious books. Do not believe in anything merely on the authority of your teachers and elders. But after observation and analysis, when you find that anything agrees with reason and is conducive to the good and benefit of one and all, then accept it and live up to it." \- Buddha*

While my goal is to honor your path and offer support, please remember that nothing replaces your own experiences, sensibilities, and the wisdom from others who have dedicated their lives to supporting intrepid souls like you. Always seek advice and counsel from wise elders, colleagues, trusted professionals, and experts in health, wellness, spiritual, psychological, energetic, and emotional matters—especially the shaman, poets and mystics. Yet always follow your inner knowing. Think of this as honoring and supporting your Inner Guides in harmony with external experts, ensuring you have the best support possible.

As the Buddha says, *"If you knew how perfect it all is you'd throw your head up at the clouds and laugh."*

Take what resonates, leave what doesn't, and may your path be illuminated with joy, laughter, and profound insights. 


### A Message to My Colleagues in the Healing Arts:

To those dedicated to the healing arts, holistic wellness, bodywork, energy healing, acupuncture, depth psychology, metaphysics, shamanic arts, acupuncture, qigong, chi kung, divination, psychic work, and the many other powerful practices beyond the confines of Western medicine- This book is written with this world in mind:

The work of healing and wellness demands openness to mystery, awe, and humility, honoring the true order of Nature’s harmony and balance within reality's ultimate complexity. It is far too intricate for any one of us to fully comprehend, yet simple enough to engage with in daily life if approached correctly. This true work requires a child’s sense of awe, wonderment, and openness to embrace and experience what is just beyond our comprehension but within our reach to apply and learn from. The art of soulful, natural living revives the ancient wisdom found in nature, a task for each generation—an endless exploration of learning, discovery, and growth.

Our ancestors practiced these arts for eons, even through dark periods of ignorance and bias. They were the ones communities turned to for help, regardless of the culture or challenges. I am proud to be part of such a deeply  gifted, talented, and committed community.

Our practices have faced lifetimes of challenges, including misunderstanding and skepticism. They have often been seen as unconventional, quaint, or even controversial. However, despite these challenges, we have persevered and found ways to bridge gaps, fostering mutual support and collaboration across our diverse yet interconnected fields.

Western medicine excels in addressing pathology but often falls short in leading the field of wellness. It has always benefited from the insights and results of traditional, indigenous, and metaphysical arts, drawing from their foundations both by choice and in response to patient demand. There is a science and art that extends beyond the molecular, into the energetic field that informs our material existence, from cells to our senses. Here, the imaginal, energetic, emotional, sensory, and phenomenological aspects of reality interplay with the biological world, allowing true health, wellness, and development to unfold in life's fullness.

Many of you have worked tirelessly to integrate this work into mainstream treatments, therapies, and interventions. You have made a significant impact in a culture that resisted this work with fervent opposition, overcoming the odds by making your work accessible in clinics, schools, and insurable practices. The exponential growth in this field underscores its importance and the need in our society, which battles against massive change, depersonalization, and a growing sense of isolation. How we think, intuit, feel, and sense profoundly matters. These elements shape the world we live in and engage with.

This book does not presume agreement on metaphysics or methods. One of the most endearing features of pioneers in the healing arts is our independent-mindedness, determination, and discerning nature. We are a collective of true individuals, often considered heretics—a proud minority seeking what is novel, needed, not known, and nuanced. We dare to look beyond what is offered and accepted into what is yet to be.

This work honors you and all who courageously embrace the ways nature offers to carry this work forward. Growing numbers seek your support and guidance. This is my contribution to this endeavor. The capacity to psychonavigate, deepening your own process while supporting the alchemical path of your clients and loved ones, is needed to bring together the wisdom and practices from diverse fields of interconnected and interdependent healing.

Healers and helpers discover essential remedies, develop sought-after techniques, and serve as the creative visionaries of our culture. They have made the modern healing arts movement indispensable, driving constant innovation and expanding our understanding of who we are and what we are capable of—almost anything if we open ourselves to possibilities and potentials.

This book honors your path, our ancestors who paved the way, and future generations entering the healing arts with a true calling to be good medicine for the world. My hope is that this serves as a guide for you all to continue exploring the human condition holistically. No one element of being is superior or isolated from any other. All is one interdependent field of adaptive being.

Our culture needs its medicine wheel, mandala, and methods to see how it all comes together—to navigate the path ahead, from the most complex elements of reality to the simplest and most obvious. On a higher level, we comprehend the totality and interconnectedness. On a deep, fundamental, elemental, and organic level, we get it. However, our conscious minds need guidance, direction, and a simplified way to bring it all together. Bringing the known and unknown into a collaborative field of new ways to be in service is the goal.

I offer this homage to the elements as a way to honor a journey that has given so much and to connect us across our differences. We all find ourselves in our elements in certain areas while feeling out of our element in others. By looking to each other, we can create a circle of wholeness for ourselves and our communities.

One crucial lesson this work has taught me is that no matter how many modalities I learn, practice, and develop, there is always more to discover and refine. We owe it to our clients, communities, and culture to keep advancing this work, augmenting it, and collaborating with each other rather than competing.

I see the elements and the precepts of elemental alchemy as a way to unite us around our differences because nature thrives on diversity, deviations, and uniqueness. Nature doesn’t just hold space for our individuality; it is the very source and instigator of our heresies, differences, and innovations, providing the arena where we are united.

May this book honor those who came before us, all of us taking up the mantle and the medicine, and those to come who will integrate the past, present, and future into an adaptive path forward for all.

In the spirit of the elements,

Kelly

# Introduction

#### 

*“Alchemy is the art of transformation. It is about transforming oneself, understanding oneself, and bringing oneself into harmony with the world.” \- Edward Whitmont*

Welcome to a transformative journey through elemental alchemy. This book is an adaptive guide tailored to your unique style, goals, and spiritual explorations. You can use it as a structured, linear experience or an intuitive, interactive method. Read it cover to cover or flip through to find passages that resonate with you. Hopefully, you will find moments of ![][image4]synchronicity that honor your unique way of experiencing and expressing yourself.

Spiritual alchemy is the art of transformation, a spiraling journey of remembering, reclaiming, and refining into our highest state of being. It helps us understand who we are, our potential for creating a beautiful world, and why we are here. Edward Whitmont beautifully encapsulates this ideal, highlighting alchemy as a journey toward self-awareness and balance.

This book honors our human experiences as elemental beings. While the core logic of elemental alchemy and the elements of consciousness could be condensed into a few pages, this work delves deeper to speak to the soul, honoring what is most true and soulful about being human.

### Divine Intervention and Initiating Action

Life's journey is a dance of synchronicities, opportunities, and divine interventions that respond to our actions. During life’s most memorable times, I have felt a profound sense of divine intervention, which only deepened with each magical moment that felt both surprising and synchronistic. These moments, especially in the midst of uncertainty when life seemed to unravel, always carried a spark of redemptive opening, guiding me toward new ideas and loves.

Divine intervention doesn't just happen to us; it flows with rhythm and takes form, shaping our evolution. Every moment of chaos and every fallen dream has led me closer to my true path. This book is a tribute to the soul guiding each of our journeys, weaving through the elements of being and becoming, crafting the unique journey of a lifetime.

Beyond recognizing this ‘field intelligence,’ we rightfully call upon names such as God, the Great Spirit, the Source, Brahman, Allah, the Tao, the Creator, the Infinite, the Cosmic Intelligence, the Sacred, and many more. This awakening leads to the realization that the role we play, the way we engage with reality, matters. If we understand anything about the metaphysics of manifestation and the laws of attraction, it is that they involve both personal evolution and a call to personal responsibility and accountability. Divine intervention can also be seen as karma, the natural patterns like a sine wave running through the timeline of our choices, decisions, and the alchemy of personal and cultural development.

It is in the relativity of our place in the mystery of reality that we stay in resonance with the life wishing to flow from us while safeguarding us from the isolating and debilitating hazards of hubris, hatred, inhumanity, and more. This balance keeps us open to the wisdom and guidance of the elemental forces that shape our existence, reminding us of the holiness, the holon, of our interconnectedness with all that is.

#### Reclaiming Our True Nature

In an increasingly impersonal, algorithmic world, we often find ourselves manipulated and controlled by external forces, losing touch with our true nature. Expediency, exploitation, and superficial connections dominate, creating a disconnection from what is most human and soulful.

It is our task to reclaim, reconnect, and redeem our world. By remembering who we are and why we are here, we discover that the world supports our mission of re-ensouling it—through us, as us. Elemental alchemy provides a simple yet profound method to reconnect with and align to the elemental forces that mirror our inner landscapes.

Our responsibility is to reclaim a sacred and soulful relationship with Nature. This connection is so close that it is easy to miss. The way is in this moment, and it is our journey to realize, remember, and reclaim it. This task calls us to be more present, aware, and open, embracing the novelty and nuance of soulful living.

*“We are simply laying the groundwork, or preparing the conditions through collective spiritual work, for the next steps in human evolution. . . Each person must do their part. Nothing more. But nothing less. Let the energy world guide you. Do only what your heart tells you is right.” \-Juan Nunez del Prado*

#### Finding True Freedom

This is a path of freedom and creative agency, free of bias from preconceptions about how things ‘really are’. By keeping an open mind, we resist being blindly caught up in fundamentalist ways of seeing and impersonal forces. We discover a life that is more in tune with our nature. Elemental alchemy can lead us to personal freedom in relating to the elemental phenomena around us. We empower ourselves to maintain and direct a life that is in greater balance and harmony.

#### The Legacy of Daedalus

Icarus found himself ensnared by the cleverness and hubris of his father, Daedalus. Renowned as a brilliant inventor, Daedalus was celebrated across the lands for his ability to craft anything desired by the wealthy and powerful. Among his creations was the labyrinth, commissioned by King Minos to ensnare his enemies, earning Daedalus widespread reverence. Yet, his downfall came swiftly when he agreed to aid King Minos’ wife in creating a contraption that would help her have sex with Zeus, in the form of a bull, unknowingly leading to the birth of an aberration—a minotaur. Once King Minos realized the child wasn't his and wasn't fully human, he recognized that Daedalus had gone rogue and that his technology had created an abomination.

Imprisoned alongside Daedalus, Icarus faced a fate shaped by his father’s choices. His plight echoes our own in the modern age, where we too find ourselves constrained and imperiled by the technological legacies of our cultural predecessors and those who wield power and control over our civilization's destiny. Regardless of whether they foresaw the consequences, the impact remains the same for us. Now, we must navigate out of the labyrinth of our inherited traps and find pathways to liberation.

In the wisdom of Daedalus, liberation comes through the fusion of intellectual free will and collective intelligence. We must craft our own 'wings' to extricate ourselves from the labyrinth of challenges we face as individuals and as a global community. The wings’ feathers represent our individual intellect, allowing us to rise above earthly confines, while the wax that holds the wings together symbolizes the collective intelligence that binds us together in service to a higher order of wisdom. By harmonizing our individual capabilities with our collective potential, we may find a way out of the labyrinth and ascend to a higher order of reality.

#### Reflections on Creativity and Hubris

The story of Icarus and Daedalus not only speaks of creative hubris but also cautions creators about the ethics of expertise, the risks and responsibilities of creativity, and the hazards of overconfidence. Creativity itself is always a dangerous gift, possessing the marvelous capacity to bring about wonders while also carrying the potential for peril. Technological advancements, in particular, can create an exponential risk of unintended consequences. These can be catastrophic or, at the very least, lead to personal and cultural entrapment. From the boundless possibilities of artificial intelligence to the profound implications of genetic engineering, creation teeters on the edge of major risk.

Our ambitions must be tempered with humility, disciplined awareness, and responsibility. The myth of Icarus urges us to ponder the wisdom guiding our creations, reminding us that we remain tethered to the intricate web of the world, a distributive network of interdependence and mutuality. We cannot wield our god-like creative power without considering its consequences. Embracing the lessons woven into the Icarus myth enables us to navigate our creative journeys with greater self-awareness and humility. This approach does not confine our aspirations but elevates them. Like Icarus, we soar not by severing ties with elemental forces but by harmonizing with them, attuned to the whisper of our practical spirit. In doing so, we uncover a freedom grounded in presence and respect—a flight sustained by the winds of wisdom and the currents of cosmic beauty.

#### Escaping Cultural Traps

Like Icarus, we yearn to break free from the cultural traps we were born into—the issues left by our predecessors who built our modern, technological world, now threatening to entrap us in an AI-guided, cybernetic labyrinth, cutting us off from nature's guiding wisdom. Every generation must deal with the unintended limitations and biases created by previous ones. Ours is exponentially more challenging because our cleverness now allows us to create and alter life in ways only imagined in myths and science fiction. Living a life disconnected from nature and perpetually connected to virtual worlds leads us deeper into a cultural trap, threatening our future and that of all living beings. If driven by superficial and short-sighted ambitions, we will find ourselves increasingly isolated and imprisoned by the unsustainable course of our own ingenuity. However, if guided by the wisdom of nature, this technology can exponentially help heal our world.

**The Challenge of AI and Human Engagement**

AI now excels in tasks like diagnostics, analytics, and customer service, even demonstrating impressive skill in human-like interactions once thought to be uniquely human abilities. This advancement has sparked concerns about the impact on our careers, futures, and interpersonal relationships. Our interactions have become more transactional, relying on strategies over genuine connection, significantly eroding trust.

Yet, the solution to this problem is already within us. It lies in our intuitions, feelings, senses, and thoughts—our intrinsic way of engaging with the world. The wisdom needed to navigate and overcome these challenges comes from the continuous and insightful guidance of nature, an internal field of wisdom unparalleled by any technology.

This book invites you to explore the elements of your conscious experiences and embrace a soulful engagement with life. It guides you to reconnect with the elemental forces within, fostering genuine connection and deep understanding. By integrating the wisdom of elemental alchemy, we can navigate this technological era with grace, balance, and a renewed sense of what it means to be truly human.

#### The Reality Check

Naturally, we want to escape the worst of our world’s problems. But it’s important to separate ourselves from our tools and not from Nature. We are not our technology. Our technology serves us—until it doesn’t. Reality has a way of burning away what no longer serves us. Icarus’ wings served to help him escape, but ultimately, he needed to be reminded he wasn’t a bird. What seems like the cruelty and vagaries of an uncaring reality can be understood as an alchemical process offering course correction, edification, and reality-testing. Humility is necessary for our process as sentient beings. The alchemical process of life teaches us both our limitations and our potential. Icarus was not a bird, and his wings melted in the heat of the sun. Likewise, we are not artificial machines, computers, or simulations. It is both humbling and encouraging to know we are not what we create. They are but shadows or approximations of what we are truly capable of being as souls.

*“Oh human thing, There is not light in being a machine. It is not the hour to upgrade or allow yourself to be replaced nor to be chased from your rightful place on this blithe planet. It is not your victory to live forever or to trade your skin for some electric dream. Yours is the cosmic gene. You are Nature’s witness to times comic paradise. . . The human story is not yet done. It is not time to be post-human. It is time to be most human.”  \- Samuel Hurley*

#### Embracing Our Elemental Nature

While emerging technologies reveal new worlds of possibilities to create a better, more dynamic world, they also threaten to distract, confuse, and exacerbate our ability to remain fully human, centered in the logic, values, and beauty of our true nature. It is clear our "wax wings" are melting off, and we see the dangers of flying too far into the virtual realms, artificial intelligence, social media, and information technologies. We are losing touch with the elemental forces that have created and sustained us for eons. As our technological world exponentially influences our lives, we are urged to reconnect with our elemental nature to avoid losing what is most essential about our humanity—our shared fate with Mother Nature.

What will become of us as we transcend to new heights of artificial intelligence, information technology, virtual reality, and remote living? The alchemical process reveals an enduring, causal feedback loop. The spirit of our elemental intelligence will continually redeem us at every phase of change and impasse, freeing us from our false identities and problematic states, reminding us what is good and true about our essential nature and how to create a sustainable reality based on this wisdom. Technology will support our cultural redemption and evolution if we are able to maintain our connection with the Source wisdom guiding us and our creations. When we tune into the signals of our elemental nature, we wipe out the noise of disharmony and isolation.

Our Relationship with Reality

"The world is full of magic things, patiently waiting for our senses to grow sharper." — W.B. Yeats

Our relationship with reality determines what we get out of it. If we think we are the wisest beings on this planet, we will neglect the wisdom from all other beings. However, we constantly learn about adaptation and evolution from all levels of beings on this planet. All have much to teach us. If we believe this planet is here for us to exploit and master, our relationship with this planet and all life on it will be subjugated to our limited development. There was a time when we thought it was fine to massacre animals in large numbers without a problem. Now, we understand the devastating effects of extinction. We once thought we lived in a world of unlimited resources only to find ourselves facing water shortages, an energy crisis, and the effects of soil depletion.

We treat our world as we treat ourselves. When we perceive ourselves as objects to be manipulated, used, and mistreated, we learn to relate to our world in the same way. This awakening to our true Self, our alchemical inner gold, teaches us how to move forward positively, to create a world built on conscious living, collaborative intelligence, and, most importantly, Love.

The quality of how we relate to the ‘world of other,’ whether it is a part of our own nature or some ‘other’ in the world, seems to be at the heart of all of this work. If there is a practical or phenomenological nature to unity consciousness, it is in recognizing the third, the relationship, in all duality—in all our interactions with elements of our world. When we tune into the relational field between self and other, we begin to engage the mystery in the field, the unitive consciousness, and return to oneness in these relationships. Here, we find not only the gateway to individual transformation but also the roadmap to a life lived in harmony with all life. By acting out of a sense of common ground with all things, we can create a world characterized by respect, empathy, and interbeing. Ultimately, this leads to a day when we create a home for ourselves, each other, and our planet within a cosmos that is friendly to all.

This became most clear for me when a client was talking about his relationship with his wife. He was bouncing between the things she said and did, and the things he said and did. It bounced between intentions, reactions, past patterns, and expectations of future patterns. He talked about everything but directly about the relationship itself. It’s interesting, often when someone leaves a relationship, they don’t say they miss the person but that they miss the relationship. It is that mysterious third that unites us and, seemingly, dances us.

It is in recognizing and honoring this mysterious third—the relationship itself—that we begin to understand the depth of our connections. Whether it is with aspects of our own nature, other people, with nature, or with the cosmos, this relational field holds the key to a profound transformation. By embracing the dance of relationships, we learn to live in harmony, to co-create a reality where every being, every element, is valued and respected. This is the true alchemy of life, turning the base metal of duality and isolation into the gold of unity and love.

#### Elemental Beings in the Dance of Homeostasis and Heterostasis

This book celebrates our shared elemental nature and invites you to explore your personal experience within the framework of five elements: fire, earth, water, air, and aether. Our spirits, emotions, minds, and bodies spiral through these elements, transforming us as we bring them into convergence at the center of our being—our soul.

*“Because the Elements are among the fundamental building blocks of nature, we can use them to create new things. The Elements are like the four bases that make up DNA’s alphabet. Or, if you prefer a musical analogy, they are the notes that you use to compose your magick.” \- Ivo Dominguez Jr.* 

### Homeostasis and Heterostasis

#### Homeostasis

Homeostasis refers to maintaining equilibrium, continuity, and a timeless sense of Self. It involves sticking to the familiar, relying on the left brain's known patterns, and correlates with tamas guna and salt in alchemy, symbolized by a dot in a circle.

#### Heterostasis

Heterostasis, or stability through change, embraces life's dynamic nature. This right-brain trait seeks novelty and nuance, linked with raja guna and sulfur in alchemy, symbolized by a vector. It resists static states, fostering adaptation and new experiences.

#### The Complementary Rhythms: 

It is crucial to embrace heterostasis and homeostasis as complementary rhythms, for they allow life to take its true course. This balance keeps us open and graceful as we navigate from one event to the next, through every change, across every bodily plane. Life, as the fifth element of aether (Sattva guna, the mutable astrological state as a spiral of vector and circle, Mercury in Western alchemy), integrates these movements of homeostasis and heterostasis, of coming together and expanding apart. These are the two movements of nature, yet life is the dynamic equilibrium of these forces.

### Finding Balance Within and Without

*"Happiness is not a matter of intensity but of balance, order, rhythm, and harmony." — Thomas Merton*

Our journey through the elements teaches us to find balance within ourselves and in our interactions with the world. Heterostasis and homeostasis represent the opposing yet harmonious forces that guide our existence. By recognizing the necessity of both stability and change, we can navigate the complexities of our lives with grace and wisdom. Our elemental nature, with its inherent capacity for transformation, allows us to maintain our core essence while being open to growth and evolution.

Healing is most effective when individuals are 'in tune' with their experiences. Some are more aware of their thoughts and communication, while others are more connected to their bodies and health. We all have our own preferences and places where we feel 'out of our element.'

Crucially, I realized that the true healer is always the client. No healing can occur without their initiation and support. The process is disrupted if they are out of sorts, detached, or unable to communicate their experiences. This realization ties directly into the concepts of homeostasis and heterostasis. When clients attain balance (homeostasis), they can engage more effectively in the dynamic process of healing and personal development (heterostasis).

My mission is to help individuals reconnect with their inner wisdom and nurture relationships with spirit guides, archetypal forces, and inner shadows. This enables them to realize their full potential as conscious, connected souls. Personal growth, learned through dreams and developmental psychology, emphasizes that all elements contribute to learning and development. These elements form a circle with the soul at the center, akin to a medicine wheel. Focusing on one element while ignoring others dilutes the overall experience and self-awareness.

Creating a Fluid Balance: A state of both homeostasis and heterostasis creates a fluid balance where we can sustain our core identity while being open to transformation, growth, and evolution. This dynamic equilibrium is essential for a soulful life, enabling us to navigate the constant changes around us and within us through continuous learning and the freedom to adapt.

From the primordial music of the universe, our brain oscillates between homeostasis and heterostasis, between the twin processes of stability and change. By balancing these two poles of mental function, we can maintain internal constancy while fostering an ever-expanding sense of inner transformation, integrating this growth into the ever-changing landscape of our lives.

The Alchemical Integration of Homeostasis and Heterostasis: Integrating Stability and Change Homeostasis and heterostasis must integrate at each phase of life. Aware of the need for both sameness and difference, we can journey through life with ease and wisdom. Our elemental nature, endowed with Nature’s guiding forces, directs us toward an adaptive balance of stability and generative change, both for ourselves and our world.

This path of homeostasis and heterostasis enriches both spirit and body in the flow of existence. Perhaps this is the core of a soulful life—a deep movement from 'being' towards 'becoming', from knower to known, transmissions and reception, from learning to adapting to flourishing in the river of the moment.

#### The Ancient Art of Elemental Alchemy

The ancient art of alchemy calls us into a remembrance of our true nature as a soulful journey into the transformative depths of our being. As Carl Jung taught, "The alchemists believed that the opus proceeds through definite states of transformation, which recur periodically. These phases are symbolically described as colors: black, white, yellow, and red." This metamorphic process mirrors the essence of elemental alchemy \- consciously engaging the elements to catalyze profound personal growth.

At its core, this path involves "manipulating life and consciousness in matter, to help it evolve, or to solve problems of inner disharmonies," as Terence McKenna suggested. It is rooted in the principle echoed by Hermes Trismegistus that "what is above is like what is below" \- where every facet of our inner and outer reality weaves into a unified field of consciousness.

Yet, the alchemist's work extends beyond observing these connections. As Paracelsus cautioned, "What the eyes perceive in herbs or stones or trees is not yet a remedy; the eyes see only the dross." True alchemy demands transcending specious, surface appearances to access deeper remedies within. As Isaac Newton understood, "Alchemy is an art, and, as an art, it is not expedient to declare everything which the artist employs."

The ultimate goal, according to Madame Blavatsky, is "to find the truth" by "changing base metals into gold" \- transmuting the leaden aspects of consciousness into radiant awakening. This metamorphosis requires a radical shift in perspective, for "we cannot solve our problems with the same thinking we used when we created them," as Einstein wisely noted.

#### The Promise of Elemental Alchemy

Elemental alchemy unfolds as a path of perpetual renewal, as Schopenhauer proclaimed, *"Change alone is eternal, perpetual, immortal."* Yet this continual rebirth flourishes only when embracing the profound paradox captured by Ram Dass: "As soon as you give it all up, you can have it all. As long as you want power, you can't have it. The minute you don't want power, you'll have more than you ever dreamed possible."

By harmonizing with the cyclical rhythms of transformation, you step into the sacred dance of the elements. Each phase reveals deeper levels of soul-awakening, inviting you to embody your full essence.

 *"Every physical element, every living creature, every natural force is but a material expression of a spiritual reality." \- Manly P. Hall*

#### Panentheism: The Dance of Elements and Divine Process

This book explores the animating force of nature and the intricate process of life as experienced through human nature and the lens of the elements. In this exploration, we find the creative force of Nature, known by many names: the Great Spirit, the Tao, Brahman, Allah, God. This force not only manifests and permeates all creation but also processes within and as all creation.

The elements reveal the essence of this divine intelligence, weaving into and out of the primal animating forces of our nature. These elements expand our consciousness into the essential domains of awareness: intuition, feelings, senses, and thought. They are the elements of both our conscious being and our journey of personal growth and spiritual transformation.

By aligning ourselves with the continuous evolution of life and the divine presence within and beyond all things, we achieve a state of coherence and resonance. This alignment promises a higher and deeper state of harmony and balance within ourselves and in our world.

Process Panentheism: Process Panentheism adds another layer to this understanding. It emphasizes the dynamic and evolving nature of both the divine and the cosmos, of Spirit and Matter. Iain McGilchrist beautifully captures this idea: “What we call life is always in the act of becoming, a process of endlessly negotiating with the whole, the emergent order of which we are inextricably a part.”

Each element embodies aspects of divine creativity, nurturing, awareness, stability, wisdom, and harmony, reflecting the multifaceted ways Nature engages with and transcends our lives. This is the Sacred alive and living within the mundane world of our everyday lives. We are the elements of the Sacred and the mundane dancing into and out of being.

* Fire: The Element of Spirit and Life Force or Chi. It represents the creative impulse of the divine force, initiating new possibilities, potential, and probabilities into existence as both the forces of free will and an ongoing fate. It is the active presence of Nature, constantly renewing and transforming reality.  
* Water: The Element of Emotions and Healing. It reveals the nurturing and connecting presence of the divine, fostering a depth of being that relates us all in an emotional bond. * Earth: The Element of Stability, Process, and Growth. It embodies the foundational, grounding presence of the divine, providing the stability needed for growth and development. It reveals God’s role in establishing the structures and systems that support life.  
* Air: The Element of Thought and Communication. It represents divine inspiration and insights, bringing new ideas and perspectives into shared existence. It symbolizes the dynamic and innovative presence of Nature in the realm of thoughts, relationships, and communication.  
* Aether: The Quintessential Harmony. It integrates all elements into a harmonious whole, reflecting the experience of being alive, living, growing, transcending, and evolving. This element represents Nature’s role in bringing coherence and unity to the diversity of life, guiding the integration and harmonization process of being alive.

By engaging with these elemental forces, we participate more consciously in the dynamic and evolving nature of both the divine and the cosmos, of God and Nature. This approach brings soulfulness to our understanding of the elements and deepens our appreciation for the interconnectedness and continual evolution of all aspects of reality.

The night air was crisp with the first hints of autumn as I tended to the crackling flames before me. My son Augusten and I had made this backyard campfire a nightly ritual during the final stretches of summer. There was something profoundly grounding about watching the mesmerizing dance of the flames that kindled a sense of presence and enchantment.

As I added another piece of wood to the fire, I couldn't help but smile at the spirited orange sparks swirling into the abyss of the inky sky. My mind brought me back to a cherished memory of being a young man, huddled around the fire with my teacher and medicine man, Johan, deep in the hollow of a sacred canyon. We were preparing for a sleepless week of fasting, prayer, and invoking a guiding vision for my future. His gravelly voice invoked worlds unseen—of magic, spirits, and the elemental forces pulsating through all of creation.

Those sacred campfire nights awakened a lifelong fascination in me with the symbolic and energetic underpinnings of reality. I'd spend hours meditating on the flickering flames, allowing my vision to diffract into the spaces between, until I perceived layers upon layers of spiritual geometries and luminous webs. Elemental patterns would arise and disperse, winking at me with the promise of deeper unity.

In those mystical reveries, I intuited what philosophers and sages across cultures had realized: we humans are multidimensional beings woven from the primordial tapestries of fire, water, earth, air, and aether itself. We are not merely physical creatures treading the earth but cosmic alchemists birthed from the interplay of these primeval elemental essences. Our finite human forms belie our true nature as vibrantly elemental souls on an infinite journey of evolution and self-discovery.

Awakened by the wonder and enchantment of each moment, I embarked on a lifelong journey to integrate these elemental experiences for personal growth and spiritual development. This book is the result of that journey—an invitation to reclaim your birthright as a masterful creator of your identity and reality.

Augusten's voice pulled me back to the present moment as he excitedly pointed to an ember that had taken on the visage of a smiling face. Laughing, I recognized the ephemerality of all forms while also celebrating their poignant beauty. I explained to him that this phenomenon is called pareidolia, where people see faces or other patterns in random stimuli, like seeing clouds turn into animals.

This led to discussions about cymatics and the emergence of universal patterns based on frequencies, emphasizing that all of life is rooted in frequencies. All matter, at its base, is the dance of frequencies, ephemeral and ever-changing.

The space between imagination and reality is indeterminable, as we discover that our known reality is based on our attention, intentions, and imagination. The notion of an objective world experienced by an objective witness is an illusion. We are determined by forces, filters, and focus that are primarily subconsciously driven. The more conscious we are of the fluid nature of reality and the fact that we are ‘making it up’ allows us to begin to choose what we create and how we create it. We become conscious co-creators of our lives when we own this fact.

When working with clients, I often remind them that everything they believe to be real is, in some fundamental sense, constructed by their imagination. When I ask them to imagine a positive outcome in a situation, a common concern arises: they feel like they are just ‘making it up.’ I assure them that they are making it up. Then they quickly respond, “But you said what I imagine is real.” I affirm that it is. The power of our imagination and beliefs shapes our reality, and by envisioning positive outcomes, we can influence our experiences and invoke those imagined scenarios into our tangible world. This is not unusual behavior or abilities but a standard human process. The unusual part for most people is doing it consciously and deliberately. This is where the alchemy plays a role. When we bring the ordinary world of chaos into order, magic takes place.

Our perceptions, intentions, and focus create the foundation of our reality, demonstrating that what we imagine in our minds can indeed become real and most often does, for better or worse. The difference between fantasy and imagination is that fantasy imposes on and reduces reality, while imagination can see into the world more clearly.

In that eternal play between the formless, elemental source and transient creation, I knew this living book of elemental mysteries was finally ready to be sparked into the world. Our world is what we make it. When we are connected to Source and the wisdom flowing through these elements of consciousness, we open our fields of perception and attention to a greater field of intelligence that guides our experiences and expressions. When we lose this connection, we become increasingly reliant on external sources of information and explanation.

I offered a silent prayer of gratitude for the sacred teachings encoded in the lapping flames. Once again, the way was illuminated through the elemental gateways of transformation...

It's the smell that transports me first—the earthy, slightly smoky scent of damp wood crackling in the firepit. I take a deep breath, allowing the aroma to fill my lungs as memories come rushing back of countless nights huddled around the dancing flames with friends and family.

In this moment, I'm brought back to a favorite camping spot, deep in the swamps of Cajun country in the Louisiana wilderness, where my soul feels most alive. I remember the laughter and stories, returning easily as if I were there now, my senses buzzing with the sound of cicadas humming, the smell of the campfire, the creek flowing next to our camp, and the feeling of the humidity wrapping around us like a warm hug. And yes, the mosquitos, forcing us to keep our wits about us. But mostly, I recall the feeling of being profoundly at peace, deeply present, and interconnected with all of nature.

These magical moments sparked the ideas behind this book—a blending of ancient wisdom traditions with modern psychological practices and the spirit of the mystic who seeks the miraculous and mystical within the field of each and every moment. It is a journey towards personal growth and transformation, but mostly, it is a call back to the simple beauty and majesty of being alive—of simply being human, alive on this magical planet, and connected to a source of wisdom that is ancient, pure, and infinite, by reconnecting with the elemental forces within and around us.

### The Crystal of Self-Knowledge

Now, imagine you have access to everyone else’s crystals too. These crystals allow for seamless, wireless exchanges of knowledge, effortlessly conveying the dynamics of your inner state and the relational dynamics between you and others in real time.

This crystal embodies an intricate web of connections, interactions, and inflection points, reminiscent of Indra’s net—the ultimate network of distributed intelligence. It bridges the gap between inner and outer complexities into a singular experience of present awareness and interoperability across realities. Layers of conscious experience—thoughts, intuition, emotion, and sensation—interweave to form the foundation of immersive experience and expression. Supporting this concept, researchers at the University of Southampton have developed "memory crystals" that can store vast amounts of data using 5D optical storage, ensuring longevity and stability.

In the rich tapestry of relationships, spiritual connections, emotional engagements, and physical interactions, the alchemy of the elements thrives. This encompasses everything we know, experience, believe, feel, sense, think, and intuit. All of this unfolds within the four facets of awareness corresponding to fire, water, earth, and air with the fifth element, Aether at its center.

Use this crystal as a tool to focus your awareness and guide your actions.

### The Web of Life

The creative wisdom of the elements, in harmonic play, is at the heart of our nature. This truth is found in the enduring wisdom traditions of every culture on every continent. The ancient mystics understood that we are all connected within a great field of energy oscillating between matter and spirit, which the Hindu tradition likened to Indra’s web.

For Hindus, Indra is a significant deity, akin to Zeus in ancient Greece. But this is not a Hindu myth; it’s a profound Buddhist metaphor for the interpenetration of all phenomena. Often called Indra’s web, after the ancient sky god who presided over that realm in Hindu and other mythology, this metaphor presents an infinitely extended web of jewels. At every intersection is a jewel, and each jewel reflects all the other jewels on the web. Everything is reflected in everything else: every action affects everything everywhere. This connects with other Buddhist ideas, such as ‘mutual interpenetration’ and ‘non-duality,’ emphasizing that every action affects everything everywhere.

Each of these crystal-beings takes form from the infinite field of elemental energies, containing the entirety of all the other crystals on the web. The experiences of a single crystal influence the entirety of the web and those woven into it, like each cell in the body affects all others. This metaphor seemed strange and confusing to Western culture until recently. However, the imagery of a web connecting us all has grown more accessible as most of us now communicate and work primarily within the world wide web.

Indra’s web exists as a vibrational field manifesting all material reality. The study of visible sound and vibrations gaining form and revealing patterns, known as cymatics, provides insight into the dance between vibratory realms of frequencies and energies that create physical structure and form. All the elements of life exist in both energetic and material forms. All are interconnected and mutually interdependent.

Our awareness of our spiritual interconnection, as well as our responsibility to consciously embrace it, is critical. Returning to elemental awareness is a return to our senses, guiding us on a path of personal, interpersonal, and collective redemption. We don’t need to return to archaic lifestyles to access and apply ancient wisdom. We don’t need to destroy our technology to become natural.

We need to awaken from the trance induced by an externalized lifestyle that has lost its way and remember that we can receive guidance through our intuition (fire), emotions (water), instincts (earth), and intellect (air). The elements can be thought of as our inner guides, directing our reawakening. They are natural fields of awareness, personal states of being, and sources of insight, not remote forms of intelligence. In other words, if you want to tap into nature's wisdom, you must first recognize that nature communicates with us through our intuition, emotions, instincts, and intellect. Those who tune into these states of awareness within each moment always have access to this innate wisdom.

### The Power of Focus: A Mountain Biking Lesson

"Where your attention goes, energy flows." — James Redfield

---

As an undergraduate psychology student, I spent many weekends mountain biking down treacherous single tracks. The narrow paths, lined with roots, rocks, and other obstacles, required skill and focus to navigate. One day, I suffered a major end-over-end wipe-out, flying over the handlebars and landing hard on the unforgiving terrain. It wasn't the first or last time I'd crash. And it didn’t end in an emergency room scenario—it was just enough to get my attention.

After dusting myself off and getting back on the bike, I noticed a peculiar pattern. Though I rarely wiped out before the accident, I found myself crashing repeatedly for the remainder of the ride. It seemed that every time I focused on avoiding a particularly menacing rock or gnarled root, out of pain avoidance, my bike would inexplicably veer towards it, as if drawn by an invisible force.

Perplexed by this phenomenon, I recalled a recent lesson in a psychology class about the subconscious mind's influence on our actions. I realized that my heightened awareness of potential hazards, fueled by the fear of pain, was actually guiding me straight into harm's way. My reptilian brain, primed to detect threats, was fixating on the very things I wished to avoid.

Armed with this realization, I decided to conduct an experiment. Instead of focusing on the obstacles that littered the path, I shifted my attention to the small openings between them, concentrating on the clear spaces through which I could safely navigate.

To my amazement, this simple shift in focus yielded extraordinary results. As I directed my attention to the openings, my bike seemed to follow suit, gliding effortlessly through the gaps. The more I focused on the path to safety, the less I found myself veering towards danger.

This experience taught me an invaluable lesson that extends far beyond the realm of mountain biking. In life, we often fixate on our fears and the potential obstacles in our path, inadvertently steering ourselves towards the very outcomes we dread. However, by shifting our focus to the openings—the opportunities and solutions—we can harness the power of our subconscious mind to guide us towards a path of flow and positive change.

Surrounding it was a labyrinthine path formed by translucent crystal walls, guiding me to the central crystal. As I walked through this winding path, I saw energy flowing in a toroidal pattern, descending and spiraling down as well as ascending and spiraling up, like a tree receiving both sun and earth energies.

I could see people gazing into chosen facets, each mesmerized by the unique worlds they were experiencing within. Each facet revealed distinct, dynamic realms, all emanating from a single source. Each offered complete, whole, and entrancing experiences. When I came out of this lucid dream, I realized that within our singular shared reality, there exist infinite facets through which we can peer and find valid perspectives, all inherently connected to a greater unified whole. This dream compelled me to explore unifying principles, leading to my deep dive into ancient metaphysical models based on the five elements.

This experience birthed an elemental understanding that I have faithfully explored for over twenty-five years. The insights from this singular experience continue to unfold, expanding my life into a dynamic and enchanting journey. Many of my clients and students find that experiencing life through an awakened connection with the elements is a gift of awakening to our true nature, helping us become our best selves.

At major turning points in our lives, the fundamental questions always are: If I make a certain choice, what will the outcome be? Why am I choosing this? How will I do it? What will happen when I do it? From this, some central focal points seem useful. The four focal points I use in my life and in my practice are:

1. Ideal: What is the ideal for you in this situation, moment, or experience?  
2. Challenges or Shadows: What do you imagine can get in the way of you achieving this ideal outcome?  
3. Resources: What resources do you have or need to acquire to best the challenges and access the ideal?  
4. Personal Goal: What is your goal for the outcome of this experience?

### An Example of Elemental Influence: Sarah's Evening

As Sarah steps onto the rooftop gathering, a spark of excitement ignites within her as she anticipates the evening ahead. She intuitively shifts her energy in anticipation as she imagines sharing with her friends a new venture she is planning to take in her career (initiating Fire). Engaging in lively conversations, she shares her latest creative ideas, her passion burning brightly (immersive Fire). Her enthusiasm spreads, inspiring those around her as they lean in to hear more about her plans and the exciting implications (transcendent Fire).

*"Enthusiasm moves the world." – Arthur Balfour*

Taking a sip of her drink, Sarah feels the soothing elixir relax her, making her feel more at home and connected in the moment (initiating Water). A close friend shares a powerful story with her, and she loses herself in the emotions. As she listens to her friend's heartfelt story, she becomes deeply empathetic, compassionately embracing the feelings rising from her friend as she goes deeper into her experience (immersive Water). The connection she feels with her friends brings a sense of emotional clarity, and some deep realizations hit her. Something within her has shifted, and the party takes on a different level of significance. She knows she will never forget this moment of closeness and connection. The boundaries between herself and her friend dissolve into this one shared experience. In this shared experience, an emotional epiphany arises, a profound understanding that forever alters the fabric of their connection (transcendent Water).

"We are like islands in the sea, separate on the surface but connected in the deep." – William James

Strolling through the garden together, Sarah feels the solid earth beneath her feet, smells the sweet scent of the flowers blooming, and hears the soothing sound of water cascading from a fountain nestled in the center of the garden (subtle Earth). A patch of blooming flowers evokes memories of childhood days spent gardening with her grandmother, a touchstone of continuity and belonging. Pausing to touch the flower, she grounds herself in the moment (immersive Earth). The beauty surrounding her and the closeness with her friend become a poignant reminder of the precious gift of life and the interconnectedness of all beings (transcendent Earth).

*"Look deep into nature, and then you will understand everything better." – Albert Einstein*

As the conversation turns to philosophical topics, Sarah's mind engages with new ideas (subtle Air). She participates in thoughtful discussions, exploring different perspectives (immersive Air). The exchange leaves her with a sense of mental clarity and enlightenment (transcendent Air).

"The mind is everything. What you think you become." – Buddha

Throughout the evening, Sarah occasionally gazes at the city skyline, feeling a subtle sense of connection to the universe (subtle Aether). The vastness of the sky deepens her awareness of her place in the cosmos (immersive Aether). By the end of the night, she feels a profound unity with the world around her (transcendent Aether). Although Sarah may not be consciously aware of these shifting influences, maintaining a balanced awareness—the "sweet water" center of consciousness—allows her to navigate these dynamic forces with grace and authenticity. Too much awareness might make her appear inauthentic, while too little could leave her vulnerable to the elements' influences. The key lies in cultivating just enough consciousness to harmonize with these ever-present forces.

### From the Four Comes the Way Forward

 *\- Carl Jung*
